docker push dharma006/from:v1 it will push oimahge to our docker hub 

docker run -d image-name --> this will create a container

          ========RUN INstruction=====
RUN is used to install some packages , run some commands

one image can have multiple run instructions

=====CMD=========
after intalling we need to run as container, i.e image to container
cmd is used while creating container form image

RUN VS CMD

RUN = this is used while creating image, we can run multiple run commands but not cmd commands
CMD = this is run while creating a container
if we give multiple cmd then last cmd instruction woill be override

=====LABLEl=====
labe;ls are simple metadata, like tags

labels are mainly used for adding tags to images used fwhile filter

docker images --filter="label=author=dharma" --> this command is used to fetch your image with name dharma form out of 100 images

====EXPOSE====

expose is used to give information abpout the port that is been used for image, it won't open port

NOTE: ANY CHNAGES TO DOCKER FILE, WE NEED TO BUILD AGAIM THE IMAGE AND RUN THE IMAGE

======ENV=====
ENV is used to add key value pair to images

=====COPY======
copy files to images then use copy instruc

NOTE: docker rm -f `docker ps -a -q` WILL DELETE ALL RUNING IMAGES

====ADD===
ADD is also same as copy, 
ADD can fetch content directly form internet

add will add files form internet and untar files directly without any command

=====ENTRYPOINT======

USED same as to start the container but entrypoint can'nt be override

2.cmd can override


====ARG===
arg is used to set the instructions insode the docker file, we can overwrite during buildtime
we need to use --build-arg var_name=value

ARG can be the first instruction before form to supply the version to base os

====ARG VS ENV======


ARG vs ENV
==========
1. ARG is used to set the build time variables, It can't be accessed inside containers
2. ENV is used to access key value pairs inside container.

ONBUILD
=======
this instruction is used to set the conditions if someone is using our image as their Base image. ONBUILD instruction runs when someone is using our image as their base image.


1. take one base os, install mongodb and maintain it
2. use mongodb official image

OS + system packages + software/app installation

in docker container names are used as DNS.

when we install docker, it creates one default bridge network, it assigns ip address to containers. but containers using default bridge network cant connect with each other

docker always recommends to use bridge network for security reasons, create your own bridge network